1
00:00:55,639 --> 00:00:57,683
The restaurant CEO
who got into an accident on the river

2
00:00:57,767 --> 00:00:59,310
also canceled his policy before he died.

3
00:01:00,227 --> 00:01:03,189
The woman lost three men
but gained nothing.

4
00:01:04,815 --> 00:01:07,568
But unlike her,
I gained something from these three cases.

5
00:01:09,153 --> 00:01:10,738
If you love Han Seol-ah…

6
00:01:11,989 --> 00:01:12,865
you die.

7
00:01:14,283 --> 00:01:15,159
And that's a fact.

8
00:01:18,954 --> 00:01:21,539
I'm sure those men wanted to save
the deeply hurt woman.

9
00:01:21,624 --> 00:01:24,043
You see, men tend to go blind

10
00:01:24,585 --> 00:01:25,836
once they fall in love.

11
00:01:25,920 --> 00:01:28,923
That's why they gave their all to her,
even their lives.

12
00:01:29,548 --> 00:01:31,634
She must've seemed like such a pitiful,

13
00:01:33,134 --> 00:01:34,762
helpless woman.

14
00:01:42,770 --> 00:01:45,606
You talk as if
you know everything about me.

15
00:01:48,359 --> 00:01:49,985
Then tell me.

16
00:01:51,987 --> 00:01:53,280
Who's next?

17
00:01:54,365 --> 00:01:55,282
Next?

18
00:01:58,828 --> 00:02:00,621
The next man who'll fall in love…

19
00:02:05,251 --> 00:02:06,460
with Han Seol-ah.

20
00:02:20,432 --> 00:02:21,433
You're right.

21
00:02:22,184 --> 00:02:24,895
Su-ho, the first man you mentioned,

22
00:02:25,396 --> 00:02:27,523
died in Syria seven years ago

23
00:02:28,732 --> 00:02:29,775
in a terrorist bomb attack.

24
00:02:35,155 --> 00:02:38,450
So, do you think
I was behind the attack as well?

25
00:02:39,994 --> 00:02:43,204
All the policies were canceled,
and I didn't receive anything,

26
00:02:43,289 --> 00:02:44,123
so why…

27
00:02:45,165 --> 00:02:46,041
Those canceled policies…

28
00:02:47,751 --> 00:02:49,753
could be a cover-up for something else.

29
00:02:51,046 --> 00:02:52,339
Once or twice may be a coincidence,

30
00:02:53,507 --> 00:02:56,051
but there's no such thing
as a third coincidence.

31
00:02:56,760 --> 00:02:57,595
Lee Su-ho.

32
00:02:58,137 --> 00:02:59,138
Choi Young-ho.

33
00:03:00,556 --> 00:03:01,390
Yoon Seung-jae.

34
00:03:04,059 --> 00:03:06,145
What did you gain
from the deaths of those men?

35
00:03:08,397 --> 00:03:09,231
Good question.

36
00:03:10,816 --> 00:03:11,650
What could it be?

37
00:03:19,658 --> 00:03:21,035
Please leave now.

38
00:03:21,952 --> 00:03:23,913
If you ever show up unannounced again,

39
00:03:23,996 --> 00:03:25,748
I'll call the police.

40
00:03:26,749 --> 00:03:30,044
I'll file an official complaint
with your company as well.

41
00:03:32,296 --> 00:03:33,380
Be my guest.

42
00:03:35,299 --> 00:03:36,591
The more you try to avoid me…

43
00:03:39,386 --> 00:03:41,305
the more often our paths will cross.

44
00:04:17,298 --> 00:04:19,760
EPISODE 3

45
00:04:36,610 --> 00:04:37,903
REDEVELOPMENT THAT IGNORES
THE RESIDENTS MUST STOP!

46
00:04:47,204 --> 00:04:48,998
ABSOLUTELY OPPOSED TO REDEVELOPMENT

47
00:04:54,336 --> 00:04:56,547
WE'VE CLOSED DOWN FOR PERSONAL REASONS
THANK YOU FOR YOUR SUPPORT

48
00:05:06,306 --> 00:05:09,226
He was up in arms
about the redevelopment issue,

49
00:05:09,309 --> 00:05:11,395
but he took off
after receiving compensation.

50
00:05:12,187 --> 00:05:13,939
Who else could've gotten
that old man to flip?

51
00:05:14,023 --> 00:05:14,940
It's obvious.

52
00:05:29,580 --> 00:05:32,249
HYUN-SU'S FRUIT

53
00:05:36,336 --> 00:05:38,047
-Look.
-So it's true.

54
00:05:38,130 --> 00:05:40,090
You're definitely a professional, Ms. Han.

55
00:05:40,841 --> 00:05:42,259
-No way.
-Isn't wanting to die

56
00:05:42,342 --> 00:05:44,845
-Yun-ji went straight at her.
-the normal response at this point?

57
00:05:44,928 --> 00:05:46,555
Was it the booze talking?

58
00:05:46,638 --> 00:05:47,973
What are you trying to say?

59
00:05:48,057 --> 00:05:50,517
We shouldn't have
let her drink that night.

60
00:05:50,601 --> 00:05:52,728
-I know.
-This is insane.

61
00:05:57,733 --> 00:05:59,526
-What's going on?
-Oh, it's…

62
00:06:01,653 --> 00:06:05,324
This was posted on the Allined App.

63
00:06:06,575 --> 00:06:07,659
The main podium?

64
00:06:08,410 --> 00:06:09,787
With your skills?

65
00:06:10,370 --> 00:06:11,497
I won't hold back anymore.

66
00:06:12,414 --> 00:06:13,832
Enjoy what time you have left.

67
00:06:14,541 --> 00:06:16,335
Not that there's much of it.

68
00:06:16,418 --> 00:06:18,128
Our weekly meeting starts at 11 a.m.

69
00:06:19,296 --> 00:06:20,380
-Yes, ma'am.
-Yes, ma'am.

70
00:06:44,154 --> 00:06:47,282
-Ms. Kim Yun-ji.
-Man, that glare is no joke.

71
00:06:47,366 --> 00:06:49,368
Let's behave like professionals.

72
00:06:49,451 --> 00:06:51,328
You're definitely a professional, Ms. Han.

73
00:06:54,706 --> 00:06:56,792
Isn't wanting to die
the normal response at this point?

74
00:06:58,335 --> 00:06:59,586
What are you trying to say?

75
00:07:01,171 --> 00:07:03,257
I'm curious to see the look on your face

76
00:07:03,340 --> 00:07:04,800
when I take the main podium from you.

77
00:07:07,010 --> 00:07:07,845
The main podium?

78
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:11,306
AUGUST 26TH, 21:02

79
00:07:11,390 --> 00:07:12,516
Check out the time.

80
00:07:12,599 --> 00:07:15,060
This was recorded right before
Kim Yun-ji called me.

81
00:07:15,644 --> 00:07:17,771
What if the tip she was going to give you

82
00:07:17,855 --> 00:07:19,273
was this secret she mentioned?

83
00:07:20,023 --> 00:07:22,276
It's possible
Han Seol-ah got to her first.

84
00:07:22,943 --> 00:07:24,069
No way.

85
00:07:24,153 --> 00:07:26,238
Then who recorded this video?

86
00:07:31,034 --> 00:07:31,952
Chair Kim.

87
00:07:38,167 --> 00:07:39,459
Have you seen the video?

88
00:07:40,794 --> 00:07:42,337
What are you going to do about this?

89
00:07:47,676 --> 00:07:49,761
I found this on Ms. Kim's computer.

90
00:07:51,972 --> 00:07:54,224
I'm having a really hard time
because of Ms. Han.

91
00:07:54,850 --> 00:07:55,976
Just be patient.

92
00:07:56,643 --> 00:07:59,104
You'll be on the main podium
at the next auction

93
00:07:59,188 --> 00:08:00,564
as Chief Auctioneer Kim Yun-ji.

94
00:08:02,524 --> 00:08:04,860
I can really trust you this time, right?

95
00:08:06,695 --> 00:08:07,738
You're so pretty.

96
00:08:09,156 --> 00:08:11,241
Oh, gosh. You need to delete that.

97
00:08:12,367 --> 00:08:14,661
I guess she didn't trust you enough,

98
00:08:14,745 --> 00:08:16,705
seeing how she saved these screenshots.

99
00:08:17,247 --> 00:08:19,082
The pain of becoming a mistress.

100
00:08:19,750 --> 00:08:22,502
The man who doesn't deliver
on his promise.

101
00:08:23,754 --> 00:08:27,341
Aren't those the more plausible reasons
for her suicide?

102
00:08:27,424 --> 00:08:28,258
What?

103
00:08:28,342 --> 00:08:29,259
Are you seriously

104
00:08:30,052 --> 00:08:31,428
trying to pin it on me?

105
00:08:31,511 --> 00:08:32,888
If you feel wronged,

106
00:08:32,971 --> 00:08:35,432
I can post this on the app for you.

107
00:08:38,518 --> 00:08:41,145
One person is fanning the flames,

108
00:08:41,230 --> 00:08:42,981
while the other is pouring fuel on it.

109
00:08:44,232 --> 00:08:46,944
Good going, you two.

110
00:08:50,030 --> 00:08:52,407
If you want to cover something up,

111
00:08:53,158 --> 00:08:55,661
you need to put up a good distraction.

112
00:08:59,623 --> 00:09:02,751
This piece by Stiller
was auctioned at Christie's Hong Kong.

113
00:09:03,252 --> 00:09:05,712
Rumor has it that it's in the country.

114
00:09:07,005 --> 00:09:09,591
All this petty gossip will get buried
if it sells for a record price

115
00:09:09,675 --> 00:09:11,718
at our upcoming auction.

116
00:09:13,512 --> 00:09:15,097
Go get the Stiller.

117
00:09:16,390 --> 00:09:17,891
Whoever brings the painting…

118
00:09:19,643 --> 00:09:21,311
will be first in line for succession.

119
00:09:38,287 --> 00:09:39,246
You've really improved.

120
00:09:39,830 --> 00:09:42,124
It seems like only yesterday
you were struggling as a contract intern.

121
00:09:42,207 --> 00:09:43,750
But now you know how to play hardball.

122
00:09:47,504 --> 00:09:49,047
You're the one who started it.

123
00:09:49,798 --> 00:09:52,467
Where do you get off
trying to use my private life

124
00:09:52,551 --> 00:09:54,303
to threaten me?

125
00:09:55,846 --> 00:09:57,681
That's not the original.

126
00:09:59,308 --> 00:10:00,559
What?

127
00:10:00,642 --> 00:10:03,020
If this ever gets out,

128
00:10:03,103 --> 00:10:04,354
I'll make sure you pay for it.

129
00:10:04,938 --> 00:10:06,273
I have no plans to leak it right now.

130
00:10:07,357 --> 00:10:09,359
This will come in handy for a long time.

131
00:10:09,985 --> 00:10:11,236
All right.

132
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:12,487
Have at it.

133
00:10:12,571 --> 00:10:15,115
But I'll be the one bringing the Stiller!

134
00:10:16,283 --> 00:10:20,078
I only wish I could work
with such a competent superior.

135
00:10:33,175 --> 00:10:35,135
MANAGING DIRECTOR JAE-UK

136
00:10:38,764 --> 00:10:39,973
DO YOU WANT TO DELETE THIS FILE?
YES / NO

137
00:10:42,809 --> 00:10:43,810
DO YOU WANT TO DELETE THIS FILE?
YES / NO

138
00:10:44,978 --> 00:10:46,063
DO YOU WANT TO DELETE THIS FILE?
YES / NO

139
00:10:46,146 --> 00:10:47,314
THERE ARE NO ITEMS TO DISPLAY

140
00:12:38,925 --> 00:12:40,760
You know what, Artist Han?

141
00:12:41,678 --> 00:12:43,221
Your daughter doesn't take after you.

142
00:12:47,017 --> 00:12:48,143
That's why I like her.

143
00:13:20,342 --> 00:13:21,968
21:58, KIM YUN-JI, ROOFTOP

144
00:13:27,182 --> 00:13:28,308
Chew quietly.

145
00:13:32,270 --> 00:13:33,939
ROYAL AUCTION
THE NIGHT OF THE CHOSEN FEW

146
00:13:38,693 --> 00:13:40,487
22:02, HAN SEOL-AH

147
00:13:40,570 --> 00:13:41,655
Let's take a look.

148
00:13:43,448 --> 00:13:45,367
At 21:58,

149
00:13:46,660 --> 00:13:49,913
Kim Yun-ji got off on the 12th floor
and went to the rooftop.

150
00:13:51,289 --> 00:13:52,749
Then at 22:02,

151
00:13:54,209 --> 00:13:57,796
Han Seol-ah got off on the 12th floor
and went somewhere.

152
00:13:58,713 --> 00:14:01,174
About 9 minutes later, at 22:11,

153
00:14:01,258 --> 00:14:02,676
Kim Yun-ji fell.

154
00:14:03,260 --> 00:14:06,721
It looks like Han Seol-ah went after her
after having an argument.

155
00:14:07,430 --> 00:14:09,808
If there had been a CCTV in the hallway,
we'd have caught the culprit.

156
00:14:10,475 --> 00:14:12,227
That's why we need to find a witness.

157
00:14:12,310 --> 00:14:13,144
A witness?

158
00:14:14,813 --> 00:14:16,398
KIM YUN-JI CASE TIP CALLER.WAV

159
00:14:16,481 --> 00:14:19,651
The woman who died at Royal Auction
didn't commit suicide.

160
00:14:20,569 --> 00:14:21,653
She was murdered.

161
00:14:23,363 --> 00:14:24,364
This wasn't a prank call.

162
00:14:24,948 --> 00:14:27,117
You wouldn't use a pay phone
if you didn't see anything.

163
00:14:27,993 --> 00:14:29,619
Find this person immediately.

164
00:14:35,750 --> 00:14:36,710
By the end of the day.

165
00:14:40,380 --> 00:14:42,257
Being told to find them
by the end of the day

166
00:14:42,841 --> 00:14:47,178
doesn't mean the tip caller
will just fall into our lap.

167
00:14:48,471 --> 00:14:50,557
I wish I were the tip caller

168
00:14:51,182 --> 00:14:52,309
so I could go home.

169
00:14:56,396 --> 00:14:58,064
WOO-SEOK

170
00:14:59,816 --> 00:15:00,650
Hello?

171
00:15:08,700 --> 00:15:10,702
Captain's been focused only on Han Seol-ah
since he came back

172
00:15:10,785 --> 00:15:11,953
from Yoon Seung-jae's restaurant.

173
00:15:12,537 --> 00:15:13,663
He's completely zeroed in on her.

174
00:15:15,165 --> 00:15:16,207
Casually drop it during the meeting.

175
00:15:17,042 --> 00:15:18,168
Drop what?

176
00:15:18,251 --> 00:15:20,587
The fact that Choi Young-ho and Lee Su-ho
were also victims.

177
00:15:21,171 --> 00:15:23,131
And that all three of these men
who were with Han Seol-ah

178
00:15:23,214 --> 00:15:24,674
had taken out a policy before they died.

179
00:15:24,758 --> 00:15:27,344
Do you want to see him lose it completely?

180
00:15:27,427 --> 00:15:29,137
Tell him he can have
the insurance files too.

181
00:15:29,721 --> 00:15:31,931
I'm the one who's going to suffer for it.

182
00:15:32,015 --> 00:15:33,516
It's bad enough he's already on edge

183
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:35,727
and demanding that we find
the tip caller immediately.

184
00:15:38,229 --> 00:15:39,064
Here.

185
00:15:49,616 --> 00:15:50,700
Oh, man.

186
00:15:50,784 --> 00:15:51,743
I feel better.

187
00:15:52,410 --> 00:15:54,079
So, we need to bring in
the tip caller, right?

188
00:15:55,622 --> 00:15:58,583
I knew it. Loyalty lives on.

189
00:16:00,835 --> 00:16:02,087
I'm not doomed yet.

190
00:16:20,814 --> 00:16:21,731
Over there.

191
00:16:31,491 --> 00:16:32,492
Wait, 3386?

192
00:16:32,575 --> 00:16:33,410
It's this pay phone.

193
00:16:33,952 --> 00:16:35,036
Yeah, it is.

194
00:16:41,918 --> 00:16:43,086
Hello, Grandma.

195
00:16:43,712 --> 00:16:45,213
I'm a police officer.

196
00:16:45,296 --> 00:16:47,257
Is there a CCTV nearby?

197
00:16:47,340 --> 00:16:49,634
At a tiny hole-in-the-wall shop like this?

198
00:16:52,846 --> 00:16:54,556
Grandma? Seriously?

199
00:17:08,236 --> 00:17:10,405
I knew there wouldn't be any CCTVs.

200
00:17:10,488 --> 00:17:12,240
This has been parked here
for at least a few days.

201
00:17:16,661 --> 00:17:18,371
Get out of here!

202
00:17:18,454 --> 00:17:19,497
Get out!

203
00:17:20,457 --> 00:17:23,041
I told you that little bastard isn't here!

204
00:17:23,126 --> 00:17:24,169
Please just leave!

205
00:17:24,252 --> 00:17:26,628
Business is slow enough as it is!

206
00:17:36,556 --> 00:17:37,432
It's okay.

207
00:17:41,603 --> 00:17:42,604
Come on, pretty lady.

208
00:17:42,687 --> 00:17:45,815
I don't know what's going on,
but we're not here to arrest your son.

209
00:17:46,775 --> 00:17:50,361
We just need to see the dashcam footage
on that truck, pretty lady.

210
00:17:51,029 --> 00:17:51,988
"Pretty lady"?

211
00:17:52,947 --> 00:17:55,492
My goodness, you're such a smooth talker.

212
00:17:55,575 --> 00:17:56,785
Oh, please.

213
00:18:01,539 --> 00:18:02,832
He seems to be inside right now.

214
00:18:03,541 --> 00:18:05,251
Can you please persuade him?

215
00:18:06,753 --> 00:18:07,921
Here you go.

216
00:18:08,421 --> 00:18:10,632
This is for the goods,

217
00:18:11,508 --> 00:18:13,718
and this is for the dashcam memory card.

218
00:18:20,975 --> 00:18:24,646
I wouldn't have to show my badge first
if I had operating funds to work with.

219
00:18:24,729 --> 00:18:26,648
I'm telling you,
it's because you called her "grandma."

220
00:18:27,398 --> 00:18:29,609
But "pretty lady" is a bit much,
don't you think?

221
00:18:29,692 --> 00:18:31,820
You need to go all out
when flattering someone.

222
00:18:32,904 --> 00:18:34,656
Now, go find the tip caller.

223
00:18:35,448 --> 00:18:36,366
Will do.

224
00:18:36,449 --> 00:18:38,493
I'll stay up all night again
and go through this.

225
00:19:14,153 --> 00:19:15,321
RECORDING

226
00:19:15,405 --> 00:19:18,491
The woman who died at Royal Auction
didn't commit suicide.

227
00:19:19,325 --> 00:19:20,326
She was murdered.

228
00:20:24,807 --> 00:20:25,892
YOON SEUNG-JAE

229
00:20:31,731 --> 00:20:33,149
YOON SEUNG-JAE

230
00:20:59,801 --> 00:21:00,635
Let's see.

231
00:21:03,137 --> 00:21:04,055
That's strange.

232
00:21:04,138 --> 00:21:06,057
I don't see the name in the visitor's log.

233
00:21:06,641 --> 00:21:08,142
Couriers generally sign in.

234
00:21:10,103 --> 00:21:12,897
Can I check the CCTV footage, then?

235
00:21:12,981 --> 00:21:15,692
You'll need to wait until tomorrow
for the manager to review it.

236
00:21:17,443 --> 00:21:20,613
Then please check it and get back to me.

237
00:21:20,697 --> 00:21:21,739
Okay, will do.

238
00:21:29,914 --> 00:21:33,626
HAN SEOL-AH
YOON SEUNG-JAE, CHOI YOUNG-HO, LEE SU-HO

239
00:21:36,838 --> 00:21:39,716
I'm sure those men wanted to save
the deeply hurt woman.

240
00:21:39,799 --> 00:21:42,635
You see, men tend to go blind

241
00:21:42,719 --> 00:21:43,720
once they fall in love.

242
00:21:45,096 --> 00:21:47,807
That's why they gave their all to her,
even their lives.

243
00:21:48,599 --> 00:21:51,644
HAN SEOL-AH

244
00:21:55,314 --> 00:21:56,774
Then tell me.

245
00:21:58,192 --> 00:22:00,236
Who's the next man who'll fall in love…

246
00:22:01,946 --> 00:22:02,864
with Han Seol-ah?

247
00:22:08,536 --> 00:22:11,956
YOON SEUNG-JAE, CHOI YOUNG-HO, LEE SU-HO

248
00:22:14,459 --> 00:22:15,293
Lee Su-ho.

249
00:22:15,376 --> 00:22:16,544
Choi Young-ho.

250
00:22:18,796 --> 00:22:19,672
Yoon Seung-jae.

251
00:22:20,757 --> 00:22:23,217
What did you gain
from the deaths of those men?

252
00:22:24,218 --> 00:22:25,636
Once or twice may be a coincidence,

253
00:22:26,512 --> 00:22:28,973
but there's no such thing
as a third coincidence.

254
00:23:25,571 --> 00:23:26,656
Lee Su-ho.

255
00:23:26,739 --> 00:23:27,615
Choi Young-ho.

256
00:23:28,157 --> 00:23:29,075
Yoon Seung-jae.

257
00:23:31,410 --> 00:23:33,287
So these three men dated the same woman

258
00:23:33,371 --> 00:23:34,789
before they died?

259
00:23:36,582 --> 00:23:39,877
Ms. Kim Yun-ji must've asked
for your number to tip you off about this.

260
00:23:41,212 --> 00:23:42,547
Hold on a minute.

261
00:23:42,630 --> 00:23:44,882
Why did you bring a life insurance case
to general insurance?

262
00:23:44,966 --> 00:23:45,800
And to the sales teams, no less.

263
00:23:47,969 --> 00:23:50,263
Could you make me
a general insurance business card?

264
00:23:50,763 --> 00:23:51,681
A business card?

265
00:24:10,116 --> 00:24:10,992
1 UNREAD MESSAGE

266
00:24:11,492 --> 00:24:12,577
This is the management office.

267
00:24:12,660 --> 00:24:14,620
Upon reviewing the CCTV footage,

268
00:24:14,704 --> 00:24:16,706
the courier works for Dallyeo Quick.

269
00:24:23,087 --> 00:24:24,380
Good morning.

270
00:24:24,463 --> 00:24:25,882
You're here early, Ms. Han.

271
00:24:25,965 --> 00:24:27,216
Sang-mi.

272
00:24:28,176 --> 00:24:30,344
Which courier service do we use?

273
00:24:30,428 --> 00:24:32,430
Dallyeo Quick.
Do you need to send something?

274
00:24:34,849 --> 00:24:36,350
Can I get their phone number?

275
00:24:42,273 --> 00:24:43,441
Seol-ah.

276
00:24:44,317 --> 00:24:46,360
Did you send me that wine?

277
00:24:50,239 --> 00:24:51,699
If you wanted it to be a secret,

278
00:24:51,782 --> 00:24:53,951
you shouldn't have used the same courier
the company uses.

279
00:24:54,035 --> 00:24:55,953
The pick-up location was your house.

280
00:25:00,666 --> 00:25:01,792
What was your intention?

281
00:25:01,876 --> 00:25:03,961
Did you want me to feel guilty?

282
00:25:07,798 --> 00:25:10,635
Are you also trying to prove
that I killed Seung-jae?

283
00:25:14,639 --> 00:25:16,557
Seung-jae asked me to do it.

284
00:25:19,852 --> 00:25:20,853
I'm sorry.

285
00:25:20,937 --> 00:25:22,480
I should've told you.

286
00:25:26,651 --> 00:25:27,526
Eun-hyuk.

287
00:25:29,237 --> 00:25:31,489
Forget it.
We'll talk about it some other time.

288
00:25:34,075 --> 00:25:36,244
We should all have dinner together.
It's been a while.

289
00:25:37,578 --> 00:25:40,289
It'd be even better with a glass of wine.

290
00:25:42,583 --> 00:25:44,669
Did you like the gift?

291
00:25:52,426 --> 00:25:53,928
You should've given it to me directly

292
00:25:55,054 --> 00:25:57,348
instead of sneaking around like a rat.

293
00:25:59,350 --> 00:26:00,810
You must've been pretty shocked.

294
00:26:01,644 --> 00:26:02,687
But then again,

295
00:26:02,770 --> 00:26:04,438
any normal person would react that way.

296
00:26:05,856 --> 00:26:09,026
I sent it because Eun-hyuk couldn't do it.

297
00:26:09,110 --> 00:26:11,529
If that makes you mad,
go complain to your dead fiancé.

298
00:26:11,612 --> 00:26:12,571
Hey, Do Eun-hye!

299
00:26:17,243 --> 00:26:18,077
Okay.

300
00:26:18,995 --> 00:26:19,912
Thanks.

301
00:26:29,964 --> 00:26:31,382
What did you do that for?

302
00:26:31,465 --> 00:26:34,135
She probably came to check
because she's guilty of something.

303
00:26:34,719 --> 00:26:36,262
-What?
-Be honest.

304
00:26:36,345 --> 00:26:38,764
You're suspecting her too, aren't you?

305
00:26:53,029 --> 00:26:54,447
Seung-jae asked me to do it.

306
00:27:01,579 --> 00:27:03,247
If something happens to me,

307
00:27:03,331 --> 00:27:04,832
can you give this to Seol-ah?

308
00:27:05,374 --> 00:27:07,084
What are you talking about?

309
00:27:07,168 --> 00:27:08,794
Not that I expect anything to happen.

310
00:27:08,878 --> 00:27:11,380
Then why ask me to do it
instead of giving it to her yourself?

311
00:27:14,508 --> 00:27:15,843
I heard something strange.

312
00:27:18,137 --> 00:27:19,597
I could just ignore it,

313
00:27:20,723 --> 00:27:22,183
but I can't get it out of my head.

314
00:27:27,229 --> 00:27:29,148
I guess I still can't fully trust Seol-ah.

315
00:27:32,109 --> 00:27:33,152
Pretty pathetic, huh?

316
00:27:46,332 --> 00:27:48,667
-Wow, this looks delicious.
-This looks so good.

317
00:27:48,751 --> 00:27:50,628
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

318
00:27:50,711 --> 00:27:52,797
-We'll enjoy them.
-Please do.

319
00:27:53,547 --> 00:27:56,926
So you're our new account manager?
You're so cool.

320
00:27:57,009 --> 00:27:59,011
Please come by often.

321
00:27:59,678 --> 00:28:00,554
Sure thing.

322
00:28:06,018 --> 00:28:09,105
Ms. Han, he's from the insurance company.

323
00:28:15,403 --> 00:28:17,696
I'm the new fine art insurance
account manager,

324
00:28:18,614 --> 00:28:19,532
Cha Woo-seok.

325
00:28:21,450 --> 00:28:23,244
I look forward to working with you,

326
00:28:24,203 --> 00:28:25,287
Chief Auctioneer Han Seol-ah.

327
00:28:29,500 --> 00:28:30,626
Nice to meet you.

328
00:28:33,295 --> 00:28:36,590
I've been put in charge of
the fine art insurance responsibilities.

329
00:28:37,174 --> 00:28:38,134
I'll do it.

330
00:28:39,051 --> 00:28:39,885
Okay.

331
00:28:43,013 --> 00:28:44,390
This is your first day,

332
00:28:44,473 --> 00:28:46,267
so I'll give you a tour
of the auction house.

333
00:28:46,350 --> 00:28:47,435
Shall we?

334
00:29:06,495 --> 00:29:09,331
Don't even think about
asking for a new account manager.

335
00:29:09,957 --> 00:29:12,376
It doesn't matter to me
as long as you do your job well.

336
00:29:15,004 --> 00:29:16,922
When it comes to risk management,
I like to handle it myself.

337
00:29:22,720 --> 00:29:24,180
Each ID badge

338
00:29:24,263 --> 00:29:26,140
has a different clearance level
depending on the holder's position.

339
00:29:26,223 --> 00:29:29,226
The storage vault
that carries consigned artworks

340
00:29:29,310 --> 00:29:33,314
is equipped
with the highest level of security,

341
00:29:34,064 --> 00:29:36,400
which means
it's not a place anyone can enter.

342
00:29:37,985 --> 00:29:40,321
I guess the chief auctioneer
has access to all areas

343
00:29:40,404 --> 00:29:42,740
and knows the building layout
better than anyone.

344
00:29:43,574 --> 00:29:46,160
For example, CCTV blind spots

345
00:29:46,243 --> 00:29:48,913
or ways to get to the rooftop
without being seen.

346
00:30:10,392 --> 00:30:14,980
The storage vault is maintained at 20°C
and 50% humidity at all times.

347
00:30:15,773 --> 00:30:19,235
The stored artworks are protected against
flood, fire, and earthquake damage

348
00:30:19,318 --> 00:30:21,278
by double exterior walls
and blast-resistant doors.

349
00:30:44,426 --> 00:30:47,972
A few years ago, the Seoul Museum of Art
held a Renoir exhibition.

350
00:30:48,639 --> 00:30:52,142
The total insured value
of the displayed artworks at the time

351
00:30:52,226 --> 00:30:53,435
was one trillion won.

352
00:30:55,563 --> 00:30:57,773
Likewise, the artworks
in this storage vault…

353
00:30:58,315 --> 00:31:00,067
In the event of damage, destruction,

354
00:31:00,818 --> 00:31:02,486
or theft,

355
00:31:03,487 --> 00:31:04,697
we'd have to cover it.

356
00:31:13,205 --> 00:31:14,373
I watched the video.

357
00:31:18,586 --> 00:31:20,045
You're calmer than I expected.

358
00:31:23,173 --> 00:31:26,343
What was Kim Yun-ji trying to reveal
before she was murdered?

359
00:31:32,099 --> 00:31:34,768
Perhaps the secret behind the deaths
of Han Seol-ah's men?

360
00:31:40,649 --> 00:31:43,861
You're convinced I killed them,
yet you have no evidence.

361
00:31:43,944 --> 00:31:46,614
And you still want to know why they died.

362
00:31:50,367 --> 00:31:53,287
Is that why you came all the way here
under the pretense of work?

363
00:31:56,957 --> 00:31:57,958
I see you're well aware.

364
00:32:00,169 --> 00:32:01,003
So?

365
00:32:02,254 --> 00:32:03,505
Did you decide on your next man?

366
00:32:20,773 --> 00:32:23,651
Step aside if you don't want to cause
any misunderstandings.

367
00:32:25,194 --> 00:32:28,322
There are people in the monitoring room
watching us right now.

368
00:32:50,886 --> 00:32:52,554
Moving forward,
meetings without prior notice

369
00:32:52,638 --> 00:32:53,639
won't be allowed.

370
00:32:53,722 --> 00:32:55,683
If things don't run smoothly,

371
00:32:55,766 --> 00:32:57,267
it won't be the account manager
who gets replaced.

372
00:32:57,351 --> 00:32:58,602
It'll be the company.

373
00:32:58,686 --> 00:32:59,520
Goodbye, then.

374
00:33:12,783 --> 00:33:14,118
CHARITY AUCTION TO SUPPORT EMERGING
ARTISTS IN PARTNERSHIP WITH TAEMYUNG

375
00:33:14,201 --> 00:33:16,495
They got rid of everything,
including Kim Yun-ji's computer.

376
00:33:16,578 --> 00:33:17,621
What about her car?

377
00:33:17,705 --> 00:33:20,290
I looked everywhere near her place,
but I can't find it.

378
00:33:22,584 --> 00:33:26,630
Her car insurance is still valid,
so I don't think they got rid of it yet.

379
00:33:33,178 --> 00:33:34,263
I think I know where it is.

380
00:33:56,452 --> 00:33:59,037
It's 132M 3925.

381
00:34:00,247 --> 00:34:01,540
That's Kim Yun-ji's license plate number.

382
00:34:01,623 --> 00:34:03,125
132M 3925

383
00:34:33,655 --> 00:34:34,739
PARKING PASS

384
00:34:46,043 --> 00:34:47,127
"Luen Palace"?

385
00:35:02,684 --> 00:35:04,812
I can't believe you haven't eaten yet.

386
00:35:04,895 --> 00:35:07,397
Come on, don't read too much into it.

387
00:35:08,941 --> 00:35:10,442
I'm sure Seung-jae

388
00:35:11,026 --> 00:35:14,154
just meant it as a surprise gift.

389
00:35:14,238 --> 00:35:16,240
Eun-hye's just overreacting.

390
00:35:16,323 --> 00:35:19,368
She's such a rude little brat.

391
00:35:19,451 --> 00:35:21,161
She should be grateful to you.

392
00:35:29,294 --> 00:35:30,128
Over here.

393
00:35:32,214 --> 00:35:33,215
Well, look who it is.

394
00:35:33,715 --> 00:35:37,052
What brings Mr. Cha from general insurance
to our life insurance team dinner?

395
00:35:38,220 --> 00:35:40,931
-Have I been fired?
-You had your business card made,

396
00:35:41,014 --> 00:35:42,683
so you might as well
just stay in general insurance.

397
00:35:42,766 --> 00:35:44,560
Mr. Ahn will do everything from now on.

398
00:35:44,643 --> 00:35:46,645
Hey, congratulations on passing the exam.

399
00:35:46,728 --> 00:35:47,563
Thank you!

400
00:35:48,146 --> 00:35:49,189
I'll do my best!

401
00:35:53,318 --> 00:35:56,864
You know, a certificate alone
doesn't make you an SIU investigator.

402
00:35:56,947 --> 00:35:58,866
You need to have Cha-cha's tenacity.

403
00:35:58,949 --> 00:36:00,909
He dug into Han Seol-ah
and found a string of cases.

404
00:36:00,993 --> 00:36:03,495
You have to be driven by curiosity

405
00:36:03,579 --> 00:36:05,414
to be able to do this kind of work.

406
00:36:05,497 --> 00:36:08,876
Mr. Cha, do you instinctively know
that a crime has taken place

407
00:36:08,959 --> 00:36:12,045
just by looking at a case?

408
00:36:12,129 --> 00:36:13,380
No, I don't.

409
00:36:13,463 --> 00:36:14,715
It's just that if I miss anything,

410
00:36:15,757 --> 00:36:17,301
there will be more victims,

411
00:36:17,926 --> 00:36:19,428
like Chae-rin and my sister.

412
00:36:19,511 --> 00:36:20,846
I don't want to make that mistake again.

413
00:36:22,472 --> 00:36:25,726
Come on, have a drink.

414
00:36:28,520 --> 00:36:30,147
This strong sense of duty
and responsibility

415
00:36:30,230 --> 00:36:33,400
is the SIU's core principle, got it?

416
00:36:34,192 --> 00:36:35,277
So do your best, okay?

417
00:36:35,360 --> 00:36:36,361
-Will do, sir.
-Good.

418
00:36:36,445 --> 00:36:37,321
Here.

419
00:36:37,946 --> 00:36:40,032
Your first mission
as an official SIU investigator.

420
00:36:40,532 --> 00:36:41,575
What is it?

421
00:36:43,035 --> 00:36:44,703
"Luen Palace"?

422
00:36:55,005 --> 00:36:57,466
You want to know who owns the Stiller?

423
00:36:59,384 --> 00:37:01,094
I don't have all the answers, you know.

424
00:37:01,178 --> 00:37:02,220
Oh, please.

425
00:37:02,304 --> 00:37:05,432
Your husband is the vice president
of Christie's Hong Kong.

426
00:37:05,515 --> 00:37:06,475
I'm sure you know.

427
00:37:13,482 --> 00:37:14,816
A WALK

428
00:37:14,900 --> 00:37:15,901
BLOOM

429
00:37:15,984 --> 00:37:16,860
What do you think?

430
00:37:17,361 --> 00:37:18,612
Must be an emerging artist.

431
00:37:19,571 --> 00:37:22,407
Her pieces at our gallery exhibition
will sell out on the first day.

432
00:37:22,491 --> 00:37:25,744
Granted, her father
will buy everything anonymously.

433
00:37:27,412 --> 00:37:29,164
She's the daughter of the EN Group family.

434
00:37:29,831 --> 00:37:31,792
Just make sure to feature her work
in your next major auction.

435
00:37:33,377 --> 00:37:35,587
So you inflate
the prices of the paintings,

436
00:37:36,296 --> 00:37:38,423
then sell the pieces you already own
at a higher value?

437
00:37:42,970 --> 00:37:44,054
If you do this for me…

438
00:37:46,306 --> 00:37:47,182
I'll return the favor.

439
00:37:50,769 --> 00:37:52,896
THE LANGUAGE OF SILENCE,
BLOOMING THROUGH THE BRUSH

440
00:37:57,359 --> 00:37:59,653
All I know is the English name
he used for the bid.

441
00:37:59,736 --> 00:38:01,071
James Paek.

442
00:38:01,947 --> 00:38:04,574
There's a rumor that he's the CEO
of a successful start-up company.

443
00:38:19,214 --> 00:38:20,882
ENIGMATIC CEO OF 'YOUR HOME'…
AT THE CENTER OF RAMPANT RUMORS

444
00:38:27,723 --> 00:38:29,683
RUMORS ABOUT 'YOUR HOME' CEO PAEK JUN-BEOM
HAVE BEEN SPREADING…

445
00:38:33,854 --> 00:38:34,980
I'm Paek Jun-beom.

446
00:38:36,189 --> 00:38:37,441
I'm Han Seol-ah.

447
00:38:51,163 --> 00:38:52,998
CEO PAEK JUN-BEOM

448
00:39:00,088 --> 00:39:02,883
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE

449
00:39:10,640 --> 00:39:12,017
Jeez, this hurts.

450
00:39:19,775 --> 00:39:20,734
Oh, jeez.

451
00:39:20,817 --> 00:39:22,360
Hold on a second.

452
00:39:30,118 --> 00:39:31,369
Thank you.

453
00:39:31,453 --> 00:39:32,454
Long time no see.

454
00:39:35,749 --> 00:39:39,252
A torn ACL
resulting in lasting disability?

455
00:39:39,336 --> 00:39:41,129
Gosh, how did this happen?

456
00:39:41,880 --> 00:39:43,548
Well, I got hurt playing soccer.

457
00:39:43,632 --> 00:39:45,342
Oh, boy.

458
00:39:45,425 --> 00:39:47,385
Did you buy this secondhand too?

459
00:39:47,469 --> 00:39:49,262
-Don't come near me!
-If you're going to pull a scam,

460
00:39:49,346 --> 00:39:51,723
-That really hurts!
-at least put some effort into it, punk!

461
00:39:51,807 --> 00:39:53,683
It's for real this time!

462
00:39:54,851 --> 00:39:55,936
Hey.

463
00:39:56,019 --> 00:39:57,187
Don't you remember what I said?

464
00:39:57,771 --> 00:40:00,190
I said I'd make your diagnosis real
if you got caught again.

465
00:40:00,941 --> 00:40:02,109
You little bastard.

466
00:40:02,984 --> 00:40:04,236
-Hold on.
-Come here.

467
00:40:04,319 --> 00:40:05,529
-Come here.
-Go away.

468
00:40:05,612 --> 00:40:07,739
-Come here.
-Go away. Get away from me!

469
00:40:07,823 --> 00:40:08,949
Don't come near me!

470
00:40:22,754 --> 00:40:23,964
Allow me to escort you in.

471
00:40:37,060 --> 00:40:39,437
This is our private viewing room.

472
00:40:52,576 --> 00:40:54,244
Thank you for coming.

473
00:40:54,327 --> 00:40:57,164
We prepared this just for you, Mr. Paek.

474
00:40:59,124 --> 00:41:00,917
I'm rather excited.

475
00:41:09,259 --> 00:41:10,468
This piece is praised

476
00:41:10,552 --> 00:41:14,306
for its portrayal of human solitude
in a Baselitz-inspired style.

477
00:41:15,348 --> 00:41:17,100
I see you've already figured out my taste

478
00:41:18,351 --> 00:41:20,103
after just one auction.

479
00:41:22,272 --> 00:41:23,106
To be honest,

480
00:41:23,899 --> 00:41:26,610
I got a hint from a different piece.

481
00:41:41,166 --> 00:41:42,250
Why is this here?

482
00:41:43,251 --> 00:41:45,962
This is the first piece
you entrusted to me.

483
00:41:46,046 --> 00:41:48,506
I thought you'd like one last look
before the auction.

484
00:41:54,304 --> 00:41:56,097
I never thought I'd see it again.

485
00:41:56,848 --> 00:41:59,935
Seeing it like this feels different.

486
00:42:13,740 --> 00:42:15,909
I stopped by Hong Kong every vacation.

487
00:42:17,535 --> 00:42:19,913
I happened upon an art gallery
and saw this painting.

488
00:42:21,414 --> 00:42:22,457
Before I knew it,

489
00:42:24,084 --> 00:42:26,002
I'd been standing in front of it
for an hour.

490
00:42:28,880 --> 00:42:31,758
So it was destiny
that brought you to this piece.

491
00:42:34,261 --> 00:42:36,304
It felt like I was falling in love.

492
00:42:40,850 --> 00:42:41,810
Toward the end,

493
00:42:43,603 --> 00:42:45,563
I even choked up a little.

494
00:42:48,358 --> 00:42:50,235
It's called Stendhal syndrome.

495
00:42:54,155 --> 00:42:55,490
This painting was the beginning.

496
00:42:56,783 --> 00:42:58,368
I have a few more like this.

497
00:42:58,451 --> 00:42:59,911
Would you like to come see them?

498
00:43:04,207 --> 00:43:08,920
I'm curious to know which pieces
struck a chord with your soul.

499
00:43:20,598 --> 00:43:21,683
Are you hungry?

500
00:43:30,817 --> 00:43:32,569
In China,

501
00:43:33,403 --> 00:43:35,822
they used to call this loach-tofu soup
"Diaochan tofu."

502
00:43:37,407 --> 00:43:38,867
Is Diaochan a reference to

503
00:43:39,492 --> 00:43:40,618
Romance of the Three Kingdoms?

504
00:43:40,702 --> 00:43:41,536
Yes.

505
00:43:42,370 --> 00:43:44,039
She was a beauty who shook the kingdom.

506
00:43:45,081 --> 00:43:48,668
When loach and tofu are added to hot soup,

507
00:43:48,752 --> 00:43:52,047
the loach burrows into the tofu
to find a place to hide.

508
00:43:53,840 --> 00:43:54,758
In the end,

509
00:43:55,342 --> 00:43:56,593
it slowly cooks to death

510
00:43:56,676 --> 00:43:58,887
while trapped in the tofu.

511
00:44:01,014 --> 00:44:02,557
So you're saying Diaochan

512
00:44:03,350 --> 00:44:05,185
is like the tofu.

513
00:44:06,561 --> 00:44:09,356
Then who was the loach
that died in her embrace?

514
00:44:16,154 --> 00:44:18,573
I don't care who the loach was.

515
00:44:21,659 --> 00:44:23,495
However, I find Diaochan quite pitiful.

516
00:44:25,455 --> 00:44:26,414
Because that woman…

517
00:44:29,125 --> 00:44:30,418
had nowhere to hide.

518
00:44:35,965 --> 00:44:37,133
Just as I expected.

519
00:44:38,343 --> 00:44:39,177
Oh, right.

520
00:44:42,514 --> 00:44:43,348
Here you go.

521
00:44:45,892 --> 00:44:46,726
Please enjoy.

522
00:44:54,692 --> 00:44:57,153
There's something
I'd like to request of you.

523
00:44:58,988 --> 00:45:00,323
What is it?

524
00:45:01,366 --> 00:45:03,910
Two years ago at Christie's Hong Kong,

525
00:45:04,494 --> 00:45:06,037
you successfully bid
on an Emil Stiller piece.

526
00:45:06,121 --> 00:45:07,747
Please entrust it to me.

527
00:45:09,666 --> 00:45:12,961
I'd like to feature it as the main lot
of our next auction.

528
00:45:16,714 --> 00:45:17,674
I see.

529
00:45:19,342 --> 00:45:21,928
You were interested in that piece,
and not me.

530
00:45:24,389 --> 00:45:25,932
I'm sure you know

531
00:45:26,015 --> 00:45:28,935
that there are many domestic collectors
eager to own a Stiller.

532
00:45:29,519 --> 00:45:32,856
You'll receive at least 30%
more than your winning bid at Christie's.

533
00:45:33,606 --> 00:45:34,941
You have my word.

534
00:45:37,402 --> 00:45:39,070
It's a tempting offer.

535
00:45:40,738 --> 00:45:42,615
But it's a piece I treasure.

536
00:45:47,579 --> 00:45:48,455
Do you have…

537
00:45:50,665 --> 00:45:52,709
any terms or conditions in mind?

538
00:45:54,335 --> 00:45:57,005
People aren't driven by numbers alone.

539
00:45:59,299 --> 00:46:00,675
I'm fairly certain

540
00:46:01,509 --> 00:46:03,595
you already know what I want.

541
00:46:08,016 --> 00:46:09,934
Since it's a piece you treasure so much,

542
00:46:10,018 --> 00:46:12,395
it's only right
to give you more time to consider.

543
00:46:13,730 --> 00:46:15,899
Once you decide on the terms,

544
00:46:15,982 --> 00:46:18,026
please let me know.

545
00:46:49,349 --> 00:46:51,851
They're intentionally taking alleyways.

546
00:46:57,941 --> 00:46:59,234
ONDANG EXIT 2

547
00:47:22,173 --> 00:47:24,008
Wait, I found them.

548
00:47:29,597 --> 00:47:31,683
Nice, they tapped their card.

549
00:47:32,267 --> 00:47:33,851
We'll find out who they are in no time.

550
00:47:35,645 --> 00:47:38,022
This person was trying to
hide their identity at all costs.

551
00:47:39,941 --> 00:47:41,985
There's a good chance
they know the suspect.

552
00:47:56,916 --> 00:47:58,293
Luen Palace…

553
00:48:00,044 --> 00:48:02,672
As you can see,
most of the hits are studio apartments.

554
00:48:02,755 --> 00:48:06,009
I think it might be
a secret hideout or something.

555
00:48:06,092 --> 00:48:07,302
Secret?

556
00:48:07,385 --> 00:48:09,929
Like a secret rendezvous spot
for Kim Yun-ji and Yoon Seung-jae

557
00:48:10,013 --> 00:48:11,389
to have a love affair.

558
00:48:11,472 --> 00:48:13,683
There'd be too many eyes at hotels,
you see.

559
00:48:13,766 --> 00:48:16,436
So? How are you going to find it?

560
00:48:17,186 --> 00:48:19,188
I'll search on foot myself.

561
00:48:19,772 --> 00:48:20,607
Seriously?

562
00:48:21,899 --> 00:48:25,778
There are 70 Luen Palaces in Seoul alone,
and there are 30 just near Royal Auction.

563
00:48:25,862 --> 00:48:28,948
Wait, you knew this whole time
and still made me do all that work?

564
00:48:30,033 --> 00:48:31,826
Let's call in the experts.

565
00:48:32,827 --> 00:48:33,703
Experts?

566
00:48:36,080 --> 00:48:37,040
What experts?

567
00:49:01,314 --> 00:49:04,525
BBALLAYU DELIVERY SERVICE

568
00:49:05,443 --> 00:49:06,319
Damn it.

569
00:49:10,990 --> 00:49:12,408
Boss!

570
00:49:13,201 --> 00:49:14,702
Grim Reaper Cha is here!

571
00:49:14,786 --> 00:49:15,995
Oh, damn it!

572
00:49:17,163 --> 00:49:19,207
Hey, get rid of those papers!

573
00:49:20,833 --> 00:49:22,627
MEDICAL CERTIFICATE
INSURANCE CLAIM FORM

574
00:49:28,925 --> 00:49:30,134
MEDICAL CERTIFICATE

575
00:49:38,851 --> 00:49:39,686
Is it good?

576
00:49:40,812 --> 00:49:43,439
Come on now. Eat slowly.

577
00:49:44,107 --> 00:49:45,316
What, did you do something wrong?

578
00:49:46,734 --> 00:49:48,736
Jeez, what do you take me for?

579
00:49:48,820 --> 00:49:50,738
I'm done pulling wrist-bump scams!

580
00:49:50,822 --> 00:49:52,699
See? My wrists are perfectly fine.

581
00:49:52,782 --> 00:49:54,492
They'd better be fine,

582
00:49:55,118 --> 00:49:57,245
after all the payouts they've cost us.

583
00:49:59,914 --> 00:50:02,083
-Where are your guys lazing about?
-Lazing about?

584
00:50:02,166 --> 00:50:04,836
They're out there,
running around and hustling.

585
00:50:05,837 --> 00:50:09,132
Thanks to you for throwing us in jail,
we're living honest lives now.

586
00:50:09,215 --> 00:50:10,758
Oh, is that so?

587
00:50:11,426 --> 00:50:13,261
But you see, the world has changed a lot.

588
00:50:14,011 --> 00:50:17,014
You can try hiding
or sitting on the mail all you want.

589
00:50:17,932 --> 00:50:19,475
But the second you file a claim,

590
00:50:20,351 --> 00:50:21,769
an AI program will let me know.

591
00:50:21,853 --> 00:50:23,229
INSURANCE CLAIM DETAILS
DIAGNOSIS: RIGHT ANKLE JOINT FRACTURE

592
00:50:24,230 --> 00:50:26,023
So you have ankle issues, huh?

593
00:50:31,946 --> 00:50:34,574
I'll give you a chance.

594
00:50:39,203 --> 00:50:41,038
A chance to run around
and hustle real hard.

595
00:50:42,248 --> 00:50:46,002
CONFIRM FOLLOWING LUEN PALACE LOCATION

596
00:50:47,503 --> 00:50:48,337
BBALLAYU

597
00:50:52,717 --> 00:50:54,761
88-2, YEONDAM-DONG, SEODAEMUN-GU
198-12, WOLGYEON-DONG, NOWON-GU

598
00:50:54,844 --> 00:50:55,887
JAMYUN-DONG, SONGPA-GU

599
00:50:59,098 --> 00:51:00,808
512-74, WANGYUN-DONG, SEONGDONG-GU

600
00:51:03,144 --> 00:51:06,272
GEUMHA-DONG, SEONGDONG-GU
SANGU-DONG, DONGJAK-GU

601
00:51:11,986 --> 00:51:13,154
YEOKDAM-DONG, GANGNAM-GU
HANJAE-DONG, YONGSAN-GU

602
00:51:14,655 --> 00:51:16,240
SEOYUN-DONG, JONGNO-GU

603
00:51:21,329 --> 00:51:22,163
HANJAE-DONG, YONGSAN-GU

604
00:51:22,246 --> 00:51:24,582
Hello, is this the key card that you use?

605
00:51:43,726 --> 00:51:46,479
174-12, SANGYUN-DONG, MAPO-GU

606
00:52:07,208 --> 00:52:09,001
-Okay, thank you.
-You're welcome.

607
00:52:24,600 --> 00:52:25,935
The door is opening.

608
00:52:26,686 --> 00:52:27,562
Found it.

609
00:52:38,114 --> 00:52:39,991
BBALLAYU MR. YU

610
00:52:40,074 --> 00:52:41,242
Did you find it?

611
00:52:41,325 --> 00:52:42,201
Of course!

612
00:52:42,702 --> 00:52:44,912
The client lives in Bangjae-dong.

613
00:52:45,621 --> 00:52:46,622
All right, great job.

614
00:52:48,124 --> 00:52:50,918
GANGHA POLICE STATION

615
00:53:00,219 --> 00:53:02,054
-Is she the tip caller?
-Yes.

616
00:53:06,392 --> 00:53:07,560
Do Eun-hye.

617
00:53:08,144 --> 00:53:09,562
She's a graduate student

618
00:53:09,645 --> 00:53:11,772
currently interning at Royal Auction.

619
00:53:19,572 --> 00:53:20,823
Ms. Do Eun-hye.

620
00:53:21,407 --> 00:53:24,869
Your identity and everything you say here
will be kept confidential.

621
00:53:29,832 --> 00:53:31,000
Are you sure?

622
00:53:31,834 --> 00:53:32,919
There's no need to worry.

623
00:53:38,966 --> 00:53:40,259
I saw everything.

624
00:53:43,179 --> 00:53:44,430
That woman killed her.

625
00:54:24,804 --> 00:54:26,222
The door is opening.

626
00:54:31,102 --> 00:54:33,229
WE HOPE YOU TRULY FEEL AT HOME HERE

627
00:58:53,864 --> 00:58:54,907
Han Seol-ah?

628
00:58:56,575 --> 00:58:57,493
It was Han Seol-ah.

629
00:58:58,118 --> 00:58:59,620
She killed her.

630
00:59:44,665 --> 00:59:45,749
Do you still think

631
00:59:46,792 --> 00:59:48,294
I killed someone?

632
00:59:49,003 --> 00:59:49,878
A spy app?

633
00:59:49,962 --> 00:59:51,922
Didn't it ever occur to you
that Kim Yun-ji knew too much?

634
00:59:52,006 --> 00:59:54,508
You'll end up dying at her hands too.

635
00:59:54,591 --> 00:59:57,011
You knew Paek Jun-beom
was stalking you, right?

636
00:59:57,678 --> 00:59:59,555
I don't have the right to fall apart.

637
00:59:59,638 --> 01:00:02,308
Then you must know
what happened to Ms. Han Seol-ah's family.

638
01:00:02,850 --> 01:00:04,435
Han Seol-ah was the only one who survived.

639
01:00:05,019 --> 01:00:08,647
What if it was nothing more
than a string of bad luck for Han Seol-ah?

640
01:00:08,731 --> 01:00:10,566
Is she a suspect now?

641
01:00:11,066 --> 01:00:12,526
You're not getting out of this

642
01:00:13,610 --> 01:00:14,778
unless you have a solid alibi.

643
01:00:17,114 --> 01:00:19,116
Subtitle: Jenny Kiim

